{"lemma":"حِلْسَيْ","slug":"حِلْسَيْ","root":"ح.ل.س","root_slug":"ح-ل-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8839","n8840"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be attached to, to adhere"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cover with saddlecloth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلِسَ (ḥalisa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلَسَ (ḥalasa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"saddlecloth, saddle blanket","examples":[{"text":"رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صَلَّى اللّٰه عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ بَاعَ حِلْسًا وَقَدَحًا وَقَالَ ”مَنْ يَشْتَرِي هَذَا الْحِلْسَ وَٱلْقَدَحَ؟“. فَقَالَ رَجُلٌ ”أَخَذْتُهُمَا بِدِرْهَمٍ“. فَقَالَ النَّبِيُّ صَلَّى اللّٰه عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ ”مَنْ يَزِيدُ عَلَى دِرْهَمٍ مَنْ يَزِيدُ عَلَى دِرْهَمٍ“ فَأَعْطَاهُ رَجُلٌ دِرْهَمَيْنِ فَبَاعَهُمَا مِنْهُ.","english":"The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) sold a saddle blanket and a drinking bowl. He (ﷺ) said: “Who will buy saddle blanket and drinking bowl ?”. So a man said: “I will take them for a Dirham.” So the Prophet (ﷺ) said: “Who will give more than a Dirham? Who will give more that a Dirham?” A man gave him two Dirham, so he sold them to him."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"someone who is clingy, limpet"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8839","headword_ar":"حِلْسٌ","root":"Hls","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of thin texture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is put on the back of a camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baro*aEap","text_ar":"بَرْذَعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of hair-cloth used as a covering for a horse or the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is next the back of the camel or other beast, beneath the saddle, in the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miro$aHap","text_ar":"مِرْشَحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being beneath the felt cloth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the kind called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * A, Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of hair-cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a carpet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is spread in a house or tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath the best of the pieces of cloth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":627},{"kind":"text","text":"K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalasN","text_ar":"حَلَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, in both applications: (A 'Obeyd, S, K:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHolaAsN","text_ar":"اَحْلَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwsN","text_ar":"حُلُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilasapN","text_ar":"حِلَسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, Sgh, K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mino A^aHolaAsi Alxayoli","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِنْ اَحْلَاسِ الخَيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of those who train and manage horses and are constantly upon their backs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naHonu A^aHolaAsu Alxayoli","text_ar":"نَحْنُ اَحْلَاسُ الخَيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We are acquirers of horses and constantly upon their backs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlHilosi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الحِلْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-ass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Hilosu bayotihi","text_ar":"هُوَ حِلْسُ بَيْتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one who does not quit his place"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) said [generally] in dispraise; meaning, that he is not fit for anything but to keep to the house or tent. (Az, TA.) [But it does not always imply dispraise; for] it is said in a trad., (S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuno Hilosa bayotika","text_ar":"كُنْ حِلْسَ بَيْتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuno","text_ar":"كُنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilosFA mino A^aHolaAsi bayotika","text_ar":"حِلْسًا مِنْ اَحْلَاسِ بَيْتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep thou to thy house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit not thou thy house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) meaning, in a case of sedition. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mino A^aHolaAsi AlbilaAdi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِنْ اَحْلَاسِ البِلَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilosN","text_ar":"حِلْسٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihaA","text_ar":"بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one does not quit the country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of his love of it: and this is said in praise; meaning, that he is a person of might and strength, and that he does not quit it, not caring for debt nor for dearth or drought, waiting until the country be fruitful. (Az, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN kaAloHilosi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ كَالْحِلْسِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuloqaY","text_ar":"المُلْقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is like the castaway"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hls","text_ar":"حلس"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is one who stands in no stead when an event presses heavily upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oppresses him suddenly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, accord. to El-Marzookee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa","text_ar":"هُوَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAloHilosi","text_ar":"كَالْحِلْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one who does not sit a horse well; is not a horseman."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 143.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA mino A^aHolaAsi fulaAnK","text_ar":"هٰذَا مِنْ اَحْلَاسِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is not of the implements,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparatus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham ibid.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilosN mina Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"حِلْسٌ مِنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A great one of men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabiyrN","text_ar":"كَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) because he keeps to his place of abode, not quitting it: but [SM adds] I have seen, in the Moheet, this expression explained by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyrN","text_ar":"كَثِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a multitude of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and Sgh explains it as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company of men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa HilosuhaA","text_ar":"هُوَ حِلْسُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the careful and skilful manager of it, constantly attending to it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: accord. to Fr, this expression, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A@bonu","text_ar":"هُوَ ا@بْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEovuTihaA","text_ar":"بُعْثُطِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surosuwruhaA","text_ar":"سُرْسُورُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonu bajodatihaA","text_ar":"ا@بْنُ بَجْدَتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonu","text_ar":"ا@بْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simosaArihaA","text_ar":"سِمْسَارِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safiyruhaA","text_ar":"سَفِيرُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", all signify the same. (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaDotu fulaAnFA wa nafaDotu A^aHolaAsahu","text_ar":"رَفَضْتُ فُلَانًا وَ نَفَضْتُ اَحْلَاسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have forsaken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abandoned, such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHilosu","text_ar":"الحِلْسُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fourth of the arrows used in the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A 'Obeyd, S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHalisu","text_ar":"الحَلِسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IF, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it has four notches, and four portions assigned to it if it be successful, and the forfeiture of four portions if unsuccessful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","IAar","IF"]},{"entry_id":"n8840","headword_ar":"حَلَسٌ","root":"Hls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilosN","text_ar":"حِلْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}